		<node ID="ID_1134520173" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamiltonian_path_problem" TEXT="Hamiltonian path problem - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_109318962" TEXT="In the mathematical field of graph theory the Hamiltonian path problem and the Hamiltonian cycle problem are problems of determining whether a Hamiltonian path (a path in an undirected or directed graph that visits each vertex exactly once) or a Hamiltonian cycle exists in a given graph (whether directed or undirected).Both problems are NP-complete.. The Hamiltonian cycle problem is a special " />
