			<node ID="ID_1844176358" TEXT="In an undirected graph the Hamiltonian path is a path that visits each vertex exactly once and the Hamiltonian cycle or circuit is a Hamiltonian path that there is an edge from the last vertex to the first vertex. In this problem we will try to determine whether a graph contains a Hamiltonian cycle or not." />
